EXTRACTED VALUE: In a little while he said, "Aren't you warm, Susie? Why don't you take off your parka."
In the middle of the night the boy crawled into her bed and asked her, over and over again, "What is that funny noise? What is that funny noise?"
“Don’t come near me,” he yelled. “I’ll jump.”
He directed the question to her. "What do you think?"
"I have mine left from today. I put them in salt in the box."
In a little while he said, "Aren't you warm, Susie? Why don't you take off your parka."
"Are you loyal to King Henry?" he asks me. "D'you follow your family as loyal Lancastrians?"
"Some almanacs contain census data." Defensive. After the trip from Montreal, I was no longer in the mood for teasing.
"You have a tail?" Now he was the one who couldn't tell if I was kidding.
"We're so happy now," I said. "We have each other. We have Joy. And Joy needs us."
"I suppose your mother told you about your Uncle Fred," she said. "Fifty-two years of marriage, and poof, he's gone."
